 ## Review Status
 
-Round 0 — awaiting initial review.
+### Round 0 — addressed
+
+All three Round-0 bugs and the tests-overstate-conformance risk were
+addressed. The two risks were accepted with narrower scope.
+
+**Bug: mutable leak.** Every read (`read_task`, `read_proposal`,
+`read_trial`, `list_tasks`, `list_proposals`, `list_trials`,
+`events`) and every creation (`create_proposal`, `create_trial`, and
+the `create_*_task` return value) now goes through `_deep`, which
+deep-copies the Pydantic model. Stored objects and returned objects
+no longer share identity. New `TestReadIsolation` scenarios assert
+that mutating a read or the instance passed to `create_proposal`
+does not corrupt store state.
+
+**Bug: submission not bound to task payload.** Added
+`_validate_submission_ref_binding` at `submit` time and per-kind
+`_validate_*_acceptance` helpers. The store now rejects:
+
+- a plan submission referencing unknown proposals or proposals still
+  in `drafting` (03-roles §2.4),
+- an implement submission whose `trial_id` belongs to a different
+  proposal, lacks a `commit_sha` when `status=success`, or points to
+  a trial that is not `starting`,
+- an evaluate submission whose `trial_id` does not match the task's
+  payload, or whose trial is not `starting`/has no `commit_sha`, or
+  whose `metrics` is absent on `success`.
+
+The driver now calls `store.validate_acceptance` before deciding
+between `accept` and `reject`; malformed success submissions become
+`task.failed(reason=validation_error)` per 04-task-protocol §4.3.
+Negative tests added in `TestSubmissionBinding` and
+`TestValidationErrorRouting`.
+
+**Bug: trial writes bypassed Pydantic validation; no metrics-schema
+enforcement.** Replaced every `model.model_copy(update=...)` with
+`_validated_update`, which dumps + re-validates. Invalid
+`commit_sha` / `artifacts_uri` now fail via Pydantic's pattern and
+RFC-3986 validators. Added a `metrics_schema: MetricsSchema | None`
+constructor parameter and `_validate_metrics`, which enforces
+08-storage §4.3: every key must be in the schema; every value must
+match the declared type (integer / real / text); `bool` is rejected
+for numeric types (spec §1.3 treats the three storage types as
+distinct). Negative tests in `TestMetricsSchemaEnforcement` and
+`TestFieldValidationOnUpdate`.
+
+**Open question: evaluate resubmit includes `artifacts_uri`.**
+Codex flagged this as defensible (03-roles §4.4 mentions it; 04
+§4.2 omits it). I went with the 04 §4.2 reading: equivalence is
+`status + trial_id + metrics`; `artifacts_uri` differences are
+ignored and the first submission is canonical. Scenarios in
+`TestEvaluateResubmitEquivalence` cover both sides of this.
+
+**Risk: `subscribe()` was a misleading name for a snapshot.** I
+removed `subscribe` entirely; `events()` is the only read interface
+and its docstring is explicit that it returns an ordered snapshot.
+A conforming subscription / replay API is a Phase-6 concern (where
+the storage backend becomes real) and out of Phase-5 scope.
+
+**Risk: role negative rules not structurally enforced.** Accepted
+with a docstring note in `store.py` making the scope boundary
+explicit: any caller can call `create_trial`, `integrate_trial`,
+etc. The scripted workers comply by construction; detecting
+non-compliance in an arbitrary deployment is Phase 11's conformance
+suite. An in-process reference could only enforce via role-scoped
+handles, which would be substantial surface for no extra protocol
+guarantee.
+
+**Risk: tests overstated conformance.** 21 new scenarios cover the
+gaps (mutation isolation, submission binding, malformed-success
+routing, metrics-schema enforcement, field validation on update,
+evaluate resubmit equivalence per 04 §4.2). Total: 57 dispatch
+scenarios + 80 contracts scenarios = 137 pytest; still all green.
+
+### Round 1 — awaiting follow-up review
